The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to algebraic structures such as $*$-algebras and their applications to cryptography, group isomorphism, and polynomial identity testing. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are likely categories. The paper also discusses group isomorphism, which suggests cs.GT (Group Theory) as another possible category. The use of algebraic structures in cryptography and polynomial identity testing suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as additional possible categories.
